Same issue on my side.

I have retrained a MobileNet model with Keras and converted it to TensorFlow. The model is ready for inference.

With tensorflow==1.6.0.rc1, it is the only operation which is said to be not supported.
I'm a bit suprised, as the doc says that this kind of ops "are usually removed from the graph".

body:
Same issue on my side.

I have retrained a MobileNet model with Keras and converted it to TensorFlow. The model is ready for inference.

With `tensorflow==1.6.0.rc1`, it is the only operation which is said to be not supported.
I'm a bit suprised, as [the doc](https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/contrib/lite/g3doc/tf_ops_compatibility.md) says that this kind of ops "are usually removed from the graph".
